**Example:**

Convert `$config_a` array into safe object:

~~~ .php
$config_a = require STATE . DS . 'config.php';
$config_o = new State($config_a);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
echo $config_a['title']; // key `title` does exist, return the `title` value
echo $config_a['xyz']; // key `xyz` does not exist, broken!
~~~

~~~ .php
echo $config_o->title; // key `title` does exist, return the `title` value
echo $config_o->xyz; // key `xyz` does not exist, return `null`
~~~